  "prompt": "When will iOS 9.1 be released?",
  "response": "iOS 9.1 was officially released by Apple on **October 22, 2015**. This update brought several improvements and bug fixes to devices running iOS 9, including enhancements to Apple Music, Podcasts, and various system optimizations.\n\nIf you're looking to update your device, please note that as of 2023, Apple has released many newer versions of iOS. It's generally recommended to update to the latest compatible iOS version for your device to benefit from the newest features, security updates, and performance improvements. To check for updates:\n\n1. **Open the Settings app** on your iPhone or iPad.\n2. **Tap on \"General.\"**\n3. **Select \"Software Update.\"**\n4. **If an update is available**, follow the on-screen instructions to download and install it.\n\nEnsure your device is backed up before performing any major updates to prevent potential data loss.\n\nIf you have any specific questions about iOS versions or need further assistance, feel free to ask!",
